    <div class="text-slate-700 text-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Introduction and Instructions</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        The Eastern Cape Rural Development Agency (ECRDA) is establishing a <strong>vetted pool of credible
        hemp offtakers</strong> to support farmer development and structured market access in the Eastern Cape Province.
        This checklist gathers standardised information from companies and individuals interested in purchasing
        hemp produce from Eastern Cape farmers and the support each offtaker will provide to ensure farmer success.
      </p>
      <p>
        ECRDA intends to <strong>allocate grant funding to farmers where credible offtake arrangements are in place</strong>.
        Your responses will enable ECRDA to compare offtakers on a like-for-like basis, assess credibility and
        capability, and present options to farmers who may choose the offtaker they wish to work with.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-0.5 text-xs text-slate-600 mt-3">
        <li>Complete all applicable sections. If a section does not apply, indicate "Not Applicable" with a brief explanation.</li>
        <li>Where precise figures are unavailable, provide well-reasoned estimates and indicate them as such.</li>
        <li>Attach the supporting documents listed in Annexure A. Submissions without supporting evidence may be regarded as incomplete.</li>
        <li>All information will be treated confidentially and used solely to evaluate offtaker suitability and build a farmer-facing directory.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

